    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka to paddle first",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka will be the first team to bat in the first match of the two-match Test series against Australia starting today in Galle.",
        "Timothy Karunaratne, the leader of the Sri Lankan team that won the coin toss, announced that Tamadani would be the first to paddle.",
        "Sri Lanka: 1. Padum Nisanga, 2. Timothy Karunaratne (captain), 3. Kusal Mendis, 4. Anjalo Mathews, 5. Tananjaya de Silva, 6. Dinesh Chandimal, 7. Niroshan Dickwella (wicket keeper), 8. Ramesh Mendis, 9. Jeffrey Wandersay, 10. Lasith Embuldenia, 11. Asita Fernando.",
        "Australia: 1. David Warner, 2. Usman Kawaja, 3. Marnus Lapshine, 4. Steve Smith, 5. Travis Head, 6. Cameron Green, 7. Alex Carey (wicket-keeper), 8. Per Cummins (captain), 9 .Michelle Stark, 10. Nathan Lyon, 11. Michelle Swabson."
      ],
